  "mythologyStories": {
    "sources": "Rigveda, Atharvaveda, Mahabharata, Puranas, Garuda Purana",
    "key_myths": [
      {
        "name": "The First Mortal",
        "description": "<a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a> chose mortality, exploring the path of death to guide future souls. His twin sister Yami (later the river goddess Yamuna) pleaded with him not to die, but he accepted his fate."
      },
      {
        "name": "Savitri and Satyavan",
        "description": "When <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a> came to claim Satyavan's soul, his devoted wife Savitri followed them. Impressed by her devotion and wisdom, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a> granted her boons, ultimately returning her husband to life."
      },
      {
        "name": "Testing Yudhishthira",
        "description": "In the Mahabharata, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a> tested Yudhishthira's adherence to <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Dharma\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=dharma\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Dharma'\">dharma</a> through various trials, including appearing as a dog and a yaksha with philosophical questions."
      }
    ],
    "intro": "<a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a> is the first mortal who died, and thus became the god of death and the path-finder for all who follow. He judges the dead with perfect fairness, consulting the records kept by Chitragupta. Souls are sent to heaven, hell, or back to rebirth based on their karmic balance."
  },
