  "worship": {
    "festivals": "<li><strong><a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a> Dwitiya (Bhai Dooj):</strong> The day celebrating the bond between brothers and sisters, commemorating <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a>'s visit to his sister Yami</li>",
    "sacred sites": "<a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Yama\" data-tradition=\"hindu\" href=\"../../../mythos/hindu/corpus-search.html?term=yama\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Yama'\">Yama</a> is rarely worshipped in dedicated temples, though shrines exist in South India. He is honored during ancestor worship rituals and funeral rites.",
